1
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:05,080
Yod's yantra. Did you kill Yod?!

2
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:06,800
Why can't I kill him?

3
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:08,720
<i>Ete-sang sappha-yakkha…</i>

4
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:14,400
I need something for my offering.

5
00:02:14,480 --> 00:02:15,720
What is it?

6
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:16,760
His life.

7
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:19,600
You still won't abandon the idea
of going back for revenge?

8
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:22,600
<i>My suffering will only end</i>

9
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:24,840
<i>when they face</i>
<i>the consequences of their karma.</i>

10
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:28,480
The forest is dangerous,
bandits, wild beasts, jungle fever.

11
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:31,000
<i>It's been a year.</i>
<i>I haven't heard anything about my brother.</i>

12
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:32,760
Yiwha said
she's going to look for her brother.

13
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:34,760
Damn it. That's asking for trouble.

14
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:36,640
I'm sorry, Uncle Niem.

15
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:40,440
I just want to see Lasor once.

16
00:03:03,640 --> 00:03:06,000
So this is Khao Phrom…

17
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:24,200
Orror.

18
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:25,560
Blur.

19
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:46,160
It's really you.

20
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:49,040
I'm not dreaming, am I?

21
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:53,920
If you're dreaming,
then I must be dreaming too.

22
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:58,640
I never thought we'd meet again here.

23
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:01,640
Didn't you say it yourself?

24
00:04:02,640 --> 00:04:04,240
No matter how vast the world is,

25
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,680
our hearts will always find each other.

26
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,519
But it couldn't be just my heart

27
00:04:17,839 --> 00:04:19,920
that led you through forests
and all that danger to come here.

28
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,080
I came looking for my brother.

29
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:30,760
He said he'd come
to learn sorcery at Khao Phrom.

30
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:34,480
Since you've been here,
maybe you've seen him?

31
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:42,680
Other than me, the master
hasn't accepted any other disciples.

32
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:47,400
Your brother definitely isn't here.

33
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:11,840
I went through all that trouble
disguising myself as a man,

34
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:13,720
and you still recognized me.

35
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:18,480
Even if you cut your hair short,
drew on a mole, grew a mustache,

36
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:21,560
and smeared yourself head to toe
with soot, I'd still recognize you.

37
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,800
Your face hasn't changed at all.

38
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:27,680
No matter how you disguise yourself,
you're still the same Orror.

39
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:31,480
I haven't seen you for a year,
yet your face hasn't changed at all.

40
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:34,480
So,

41
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:37,360
how was life
with your grandfather in Nakhon?

42
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:40,000
And why did you end up here at Khao Phrom?

43
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:43,760
It's a long story.

44
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:49,400
Are you still living at Khuan Phra-ngam?

45
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:53,040
I moved to live
with relatives in Huai Yao.

46
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:56,080
I won't be going back there again.

47
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:57,840
What about you?

48
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,440
I won't be going back either.

49
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:11,520
Then where are you going now? Back home?

50
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:14,240
Not yet.

51
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:17,560
There's something I must do
before I can go back.

52
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:20,080
What about you?

53
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:23,760
I have to find my brother.

54
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:26,640
Why are you looking for him?

55
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:30,360
What happened? Can you tell me?

56
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:35,000
When I find him, I'll tell you.

57
00:06:35,080 --> 00:06:37,000
Do you even know where he is?

58
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:40,080
No.

59
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:43,360
Then you're just going to
wander aimlessly?

60
00:06:44,840 --> 00:06:48,240
Then I'll go with you.
Wherever you go, I'll go too.

61
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:51,560
Along the way, I might find my brother.

62
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:54,560
But where I'm going is dangerous.

63
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:57,080
I don't want to put your life at risk.

64
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,520
So where are you going?

65
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,280
The Banthat Mountain Range.

66
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:23,040
Your niece has a strong fate.
She won't die easily.

67
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:29,880
Where should I go to find her?

68
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:32,400
Saturn opposes her ascendant.

69
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:34,680
Her fate won't allow her
to stay in one place.

70
00:07:35,440 --> 00:07:37,600
She must wander.

71
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:40,600
No matter how you search,
you won't find her.

72
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:50,120
I'm worried about her. How long

73
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:51,360
before we see her again?

74
00:07:51,440 --> 00:07:54,480
When the time comes,
she'll return on her own.

75
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:09,680
He said Yiwha will return
when the time is right.

76
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:12,200
Don't worry too much.

77
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:14,720
I know.

78
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:19,200
His readings never miss.

79
00:08:20,280 --> 00:08:23,240
But my niece is gone. How can I stay calm?

80
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:26,920
If anything happens to her,
I wouldn't be able to face her father.

81
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:30,240
I'll send people
to keep watch at Khao Phrom.

82
00:08:30,320 --> 00:08:33,880
If Yiwha goes there, we'll get word.

83
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:36,240
And if she doesn't?

84
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:38,799
I'll ask my police friends
to help search as well.

85
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:41,080
We might get some leads.

86
00:08:42,559 --> 00:08:43,960
Pun's got a lot of friends.

87
00:08:44,039 --> 00:08:47,520
He has eyes and ears everywhere.
We'll find Yiwha for sure.

88
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:34,280
You have completed

89
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:36,840
your sorcery under me, Lasor.

90
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:50,640
Thank you, Master, for teaching me.

91
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:54,920
Remember.

92
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:57,960
My blood runs in your veins.

93
00:09:58,480 --> 00:10:00,320
Never betray me.

94
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,680
Otherwise,

95
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:05,880
you'll learn of something more terrifying

96
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:07,200
than death.

97
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:15,320
I will remain loyal to you

98
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:17,920
until my last breath.

99
00:10:18,920 --> 00:10:19,760
Good.

100
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:23,040
Now go your own way.

101
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:58,760
<i>Anissosa imangkaya,</i>

102
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:01,520
<i>phanthanam vikungkare.</i>

103
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:06,120
Nui, you're coming with me.

104
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:22,320
You still haven't told me
what you're going to do

105
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:24,360
in the Banthat Mountain Range.

106
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:27,680
Why do you need to know?

107
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:31,160
I need to know because I'm going with you.

108
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:34,720
Who said I'd let you come?

109
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:39,240
I told you, I have to look for my brother.

110
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:42,160
He might be in the Banthat Mountains too.

111
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:46,520
Your brother isn't there.

112
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:51,280
If you can go there, why can't my brother?

113
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:55,880
I must go there

114
00:11:57,320 --> 00:11:58,720
to search for something.

115
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:02,960
What is it? Tell me.

116
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:09,800
It is Klaikot Lek Lai.

117
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:16,680
I've never heard of it before.

118
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:19,200
How is it different from ordinary Lek Lai?

119
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:22,760
Klaikot Lek Lai
is the supreme form of Lek Lai,

120
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:26,200
the most powerful of them all.

121
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:31,520
<i>Whoever possesses Klaikot Lek Lai</i>

122
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:33,720
<i>will be invincible.</i>

123
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:36,560
<i>Water won't drown them.</i>
<i>Fire won't burn them.</i>

124
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:40,760
They'll never be defeated in battle.

125
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:44,040
How do you know that legend is real?

126
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:47,960
I read about it
in ancient books at Khao Phrom.

127
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:51,520
Many people have searched
for Klaikot Lek Lai,

128
00:12:52,680 --> 00:12:54,440
but no one has ever found it.

129
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:59,760
You've already mastered sorcery
at Khao Phrom.

130
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:02,160
Why risk your life chasing Lek Lai

131
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:04,000
when no one even knows if it exists?

132
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:09,440
Because it will give me power

133
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:12,280
far beyond ordinary sorcerers.

134
00:13:18,160 --> 00:13:21,080
If my father's Lek Lai is real,
this cat won't die.

135
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:28,360
That means Father Wad's Lek Lai is real.

136
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:31,200
That's why it won't fire,
why blades can't cut through.

137
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:36,800
Maybe my brother
is searching for Lek Lai too.

138
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:41,480
Your brother is interested
in things like that?

139
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,080
Whoa.

140
00:13:43,160 --> 00:13:45,160
Men are only interested in a few things,

141
00:13:45,680 --> 00:13:49,440
learning sorcery and finding
sacred objects to protect themselves.

142
00:13:49,520 --> 00:13:50,840
Just like you, Blur.

143
00:13:51,680 --> 00:13:54,400
Please. Let me come with you.

144
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:55,400
Please.

145
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:58,480
Please.

146
00:13:59,360 --> 00:14:02,840
Please, Blur. Please.

147
00:14:05,880 --> 00:14:06,920
Let me go with you.

148
00:14:08,280 --> 00:14:09,280
Please.

149
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:12,440
Fine.

150
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:25,600
Would you like some fruit?

151
00:14:26,520 --> 00:14:28,040
I have vegetables too.

152
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:32,480
Business good today?

153
00:14:32,560 --> 00:14:34,720
I haven't sold a thing since morning, Pud.

154
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:35,960
Hey.

155
00:14:36,880 --> 00:14:38,960
I told you to call him Village Chief Pud.

156
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:41,640
The Governor appointed my uncle
as the new village chief

157
00:14:42,160 --> 00:14:44,040
of Khuan Phra-ngam, replacing Khun Yod.

158
00:14:44,120 --> 00:14:45,880
Get that through your rotten skull.

159
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:46,960
Yes.

160
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:52,720
- That's all?
- Yes, sir.

161
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:54,640
Come here.

162
00:14:55,480 --> 00:14:56,560
Good luck with your sales.

163
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:58,880
Yes, Village Chief Pud.

164
00:15:06,360 --> 00:15:08,240
Wait.

165
00:15:09,280 --> 00:15:11,120
You can't sit here.

166
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:13,760
Why not?

167
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:16,520
This table is already reserved.

168
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:17,520
By who?

169
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:18,680
By me.

170
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:28,760
Hey,

171
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:31,240
find another table for Khun Paeng.

172
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:34,360
I'm sitting here. You move.

173
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:38,320
Why do you think you can order me around?

174
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:42,120
You can act tough with anyone,
but not with me.

175
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:46,040
You think I'm afraid of you?

176
00:15:46,760 --> 00:15:48,120
Or do you want trouble, Pud?

177
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:49,000
Go on.

178
00:15:58,480 --> 00:15:59,880
Hey.

179
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:02,120
Pud!

180
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:03,760
You bewitched me into shooting him.

181
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:04,960
Tim,

182
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:08,800
you should be grateful
I didn't make you shoot yourself.

183
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:12,440
You're finished.

184
00:16:12,520 --> 00:16:16,560
You're no longer in the governor's favor.
I can do whatever I want to you now.

185
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:21,640
Let's go.

186
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:35,520
Pud…

187
00:16:36,040 --> 00:16:38,880
That bastard's getting
more arrogant by the day.

188
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:42,400
He thinks he's untouchable
with the governor backing him.

189
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:45,200
Pud has magic.
It won't be easy to deal with him.

190
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:48,360
Let him strut for now.

191
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:50,760
The day he slips up,

192
00:16:50,840 --> 00:16:52,800
I'll be the first
to crush him into the dirt.

193
00:17:12,359 --> 00:17:14,079
It's been a long time.

194
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:20,280
I'm a sinful bandit.

195
00:17:20,800 --> 00:17:23,760
I dare not approach you,
for fear of staining your virtue.

196
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:29,400
Within good, there is evil.
Within evil, there is good.

197
00:17:30,840 --> 00:17:33,000
That's the truth of this world.

198
00:17:33,080 --> 00:17:37,000
If you were evil by nature, I would never
have taught you in the first place.

199
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:43,080
But now, the magic
you once taught me in mercy

200
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:45,840
has completely faded.

201
00:17:48,520 --> 00:17:51,600
Carelessness
has brought ruin to countless lives.

202
00:17:52,360 --> 00:17:55,640
You were defeated
by your own carelessness.

203
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:57,840
What should I do now?

204
00:17:58,760 --> 00:18:02,080
All knowledge already resides within you.

205
00:18:02,160 --> 00:18:03,440
Spells

206
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:06,960
are merely anchors
to keep the mind from straying.

207
00:18:07,040 --> 00:18:09,240
When the mind is firm and powerful,

208
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:11,400
magic will regain its strength.

209
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:35,120
We've been trekking all day.
Aren't you going to bathe?

210
00:18:35,880 --> 00:18:36,960
It's fine.

211
00:18:37,480 --> 00:18:38,840
It's not that hot.

212
00:18:42,880 --> 00:18:44,640
Are you afraid I'll peek?

213
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:46,880
No.

214
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:50,040
I just don't feel like bathing yet.

215
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:54,520
You're lazy, even about bathing.

216
00:18:56,920 --> 00:19:00,480
In my village, we bathe only once a month.

217
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:03,920
Strange.

218
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:06,040
If you don't want to, then don't.

219
00:19:58,560 --> 00:20:00,720
Such a heavy sleeper, Blur.

220
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:33,840
Orror?

221
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:36,160
Where are you?

222
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:03,880
Oh, I thought you were tough.

223
00:21:03,960 --> 00:21:06,080
Turns out you just ran off to bathe alone.

224
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:15,920
Blur! Were you peeping at me?

225
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:19,000
No. I didn't mean to.

226
00:21:19,080 --> 00:21:21,720
Didn't mean to? You're clearly looking.

227
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:25,560
I can't see anything.

228
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:28,080
What do you mean you can't see?
You're standing right there.

229
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:29,720
Get out.

230
00:21:29,800 --> 00:21:32,480
- Go.
- Alright. I'm going.

231
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:48,680
What are you laughing at?

232
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:52,440
Didn't you say people in your village
bathe only once a month?

233
00:21:53,560 --> 00:21:56,800
I forgot, today just happens
to be the one-month mark.

234
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:01,960
Why are you shy?

235
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:04,320
One day,
I'll ask you to be my wife anyway.

236
00:22:07,520 --> 00:22:10,080
And who said I'd be your wife?

237
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:17,600
There's an old saying. "Three days away
from a woman and the heart may change."

238
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:21,160
Don't you think

239
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:23,920
the one who changes
might not be the woman?

240
00:22:24,480 --> 00:22:27,320
Maybe it's the man, fickle

241
00:22:27,400 --> 00:22:29,440
as a buffalo-dung fence post.

242
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:32,200
He loves whoever's nearby.

243
00:22:32,280 --> 00:22:35,080
New love replaces the old,
the turtle replaces the dog.

244
00:22:43,080 --> 00:22:44,880
You are my first love.

245
00:22:47,360 --> 00:22:48,880
How could I ever forget you?

246
00:22:55,720 --> 00:22:56,960
What about you?

247
00:22:58,200 --> 00:22:59,840
Do you still love me the same?

248
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:10,280
Yes.

249
00:23:17,720 --> 00:23:19,000
Can I believe you?

250
00:23:26,040 --> 00:23:27,720
If you don't believe me, than don't.

251
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:34,560
I believe you.

252
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:27,680
<i>Jijeruni jittang</i>

253
00:24:29,080 --> 00:24:30,880
<i>jetasikang rupang</i>

254
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:34,400
<i>nibbhanang manapatha</i>

255
00:24:34,480 --> 00:24:37,120
<i>pathavi dhatu dighangwa</i>

256
00:24:37,200 --> 00:24:40,520
<i>bhakasaja jivang uttehi…</i>

257
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:18,840
I've awakened you, Nui.

258
00:25:19,760 --> 00:25:23,520
From now on, you will be with me forever.

259
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:32,040
Brother, I'm hungry.

260
00:26:20,360 --> 00:26:22,680
We're closed on Wednesdays.
Come back another day.

261
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:29,760
I'm not here for a haircut.

262
00:26:34,520 --> 00:26:37,680
This is a barbershop.
If you're not here for a haircut,

263
00:26:38,200 --> 00:26:40,080
you're in the wrong place.

264
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:42,560
Is this Uncle Chaem's house?

265
00:26:42,640 --> 00:26:44,280
You know my father?

266
00:26:49,320 --> 00:26:50,280
Talong.

267
00:26:56,800 --> 00:26:57,800
Uncle.

268
00:27:09,160 --> 00:27:10,960
When did you return from Penang?

269
00:27:11,040 --> 00:27:13,720
Last month, Uncle.
After finishing my studies,

270
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:16,320
I hurried back
to help with the family business.

271
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:20,040
I plan to expand
our business here in Huai Yao.

272
00:27:21,680 --> 00:27:23,920
How is Chin Yuan, Talong?

273
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:25,760
My father is well.

274
00:27:26,280 --> 00:27:28,600
He asked me to bring tea leaves from China

275
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:31,080
for Uncle Chaem and Uncle Niem.

276
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:33,600
Let me see.

277
00:27:40,560 --> 00:27:42,000
It smells good.

278
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:43,440
It must be expensive.

279
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:47,600
Who knows if it's even drinkable.

280
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:50,000
Chang, come here.

281
00:27:50,080 --> 00:27:51,160
What, Uncle?

282
00:27:52,680 --> 00:27:53,640
Such bad manners.

283
00:27:53,720 --> 00:27:55,360
You may not know,

284
00:27:55,440 --> 00:27:59,240
my father's tea plantation in Fujian
requires reservations a year in advance.

285
00:27:59,320 --> 00:28:02,000
Even with money, there's no guarantee
you'll get to taste it.

286
00:28:05,280 --> 00:28:06,400
That house,

287
00:28:07,240 --> 00:28:09,320
Chin Yuan bought it years ago.

288
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:11,240
It's old, but still livable.

289
00:28:12,800 --> 00:28:15,920
While you're staying here, I'll have Noree

290
00:28:16,600 --> 00:28:18,920
take care of your meals and lodging.

291
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:22,200
If you need anything, just tell her.

292
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:25,440
Yes.

293
00:28:28,640 --> 00:28:30,080
I'm a man.

294
00:28:30,160 --> 00:28:32,600
Staying alone with Noree
wouldn't be appropriate.

295
00:28:32,680 --> 00:28:35,160
It might invite gossip.

296
00:28:40,760 --> 00:28:42,960
Then Chang can take care of Talong.

297
00:28:43,640 --> 00:28:45,040
No way, Uncle.

298
00:28:45,880 --> 00:28:47,560
I don't know how to take care of anyone,

299
00:28:48,080 --> 00:28:49,880
especially someone so demanding.

300
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:53,560
Don't be lazy.

301
00:28:54,200 --> 00:28:56,480
You, Chang. Go stay with Talong.

302
00:28:56,560 --> 00:28:58,440
No, Dad.

303
00:29:10,880 --> 00:29:14,800
Please protect Yiwha from all danger

304
00:29:15,320 --> 00:29:17,720
and bring her back safely soon.

305
00:29:17,800 --> 00:29:19,880
So Pun can finally stop being sad.

306
00:29:32,920 --> 00:29:34,000
Watch out.

307
00:29:42,640 --> 00:29:44,480
I'm so clumsy.

308
00:29:45,600 --> 00:29:46,840
Let me help.

309
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:20,600
Isn't Chang with you?

310
00:30:21,360 --> 00:30:23,600
He's looking after an important guest.

311
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:25,520
Who?

312
00:30:26,040 --> 00:30:28,120
Young Master Talong, Chin Yuan's son.

313
00:30:29,600 --> 00:30:33,240
Chin Yuan is very close to my father.

314
00:30:33,320 --> 00:30:34,920
They do business together often.

315
00:30:36,040 --> 00:30:37,560
I should probably

316
00:30:38,320 --> 00:30:40,120
pay him a visit sometime.

317
00:30:42,600 --> 00:30:46,360
Whenever you come, just let me know.
I'll make <i>moo hong</i> for you.

318
00:30:47,440 --> 00:30:49,080
You know that's my favorite?

319
00:30:55,520 --> 00:30:57,680
I'll be looking forward
to tasting your cooking, Noree.

320
00:31:57,760 --> 00:31:58,920
Can I go now?

321
00:32:01,880 --> 00:32:02,880
Not yet.

322
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:05,840
Uncle Chaem told you
to stay and attend to me.

323
00:32:07,840 --> 00:32:09,640
My father told me to keep you company,

324
00:32:10,520 --> 00:32:11,960
not to be your servant.

325
00:32:14,040 --> 00:32:15,280
It's the same thing.

326
00:32:16,280 --> 00:32:19,520
Either way,
you'll be staying here with me.

327
00:32:21,960 --> 00:32:23,520
Damn it…

328
00:32:31,560 --> 00:32:33,400
Change the bedsheets for me.

329
00:32:36,440 --> 00:32:37,640
Why?

330
00:32:38,960 --> 00:32:40,400
I'm allergic to dust.

331
00:32:40,480 --> 00:32:42,160
What dust?

332
00:32:43,160 --> 00:32:45,160
This place is cleaner than my own room.

333
00:32:48,840 --> 00:32:51,720
Change them. I can't sleep like this.

334
00:32:53,360 --> 00:32:54,320
Whoa.

335
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:25,240
So damn picky.
He bosses me around worse than a slave.

336
00:33:27,600 --> 00:33:28,560
Chang!

337
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:42,400
What now?

338
00:33:46,840 --> 00:33:48,320
Scrub my back for me.

339
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:50,960
It's your back. Scrub it yourself.

340
00:33:56,840 --> 00:33:58,520
I can't reach.

341
00:34:02,400 --> 00:34:03,840
Can you do anything by yourself?

342
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:19,320
Do you find me repulsive?

343
00:34:22,560 --> 00:34:23,719
No.

344
00:34:23,800 --> 00:34:25,800
I've just never done this
for anyone before.

345
00:34:32,120 --> 00:34:33,800
Then I'm your first.

346
00:34:35,719 --> 00:34:36,880
Yeah.

347
00:34:42,480 --> 00:34:45,760
My father sent me here
to scout land for warehouse construction.

348
00:34:46,639 --> 00:34:48,719
I'll probably be troubling you
for quite a while.

349
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:55,400
At least you know that.
Try not to use me so much next time.

350
00:35:03,400 --> 00:35:05,640
Bring a towel and dry me.

351
00:35:21,840 --> 00:35:25,920
We've walked so far
and still can't find the way out.

352
00:35:26,440 --> 00:35:28,160
I think we're lost.

353
00:35:30,440 --> 00:35:33,040
It must be the forest's enchantment
clouding our sight.

354
00:35:33,120 --> 00:35:34,600
Don't blame the forest.

355
00:35:34,680 --> 00:35:37,480
You're the one who got us lost, Blur.

356
00:35:40,840 --> 00:35:43,800
It's almost dark. We'll have to camp here.

357
00:35:44,640 --> 00:35:47,360
Wait here. I'll go find some firewood.

358
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:50,600
Blur.

359
00:35:51,840 --> 00:35:53,840
Look over there. Lights.

360
00:35:54,360 --> 00:35:56,200
There must be a village.

361
00:35:59,080 --> 00:36:01,320
Deep in the forest like this,
it's unlikely there'd be one.

362
00:36:02,440 --> 00:36:03,680
Come on.

363
00:36:04,400 --> 00:36:05,240
Let's go.

364
00:36:09,200 --> 00:36:10,320
Hey.

365
00:36:22,720 --> 00:36:23,960
Hello.

366
00:36:24,040 --> 00:36:24,880
Hello.

367
00:36:24,960 --> 00:36:27,600
Where are you two headed?

368
00:36:28,240 --> 00:36:31,160
We're on our way
to visit relatives in another town.

369
00:36:31,240 --> 00:36:32,760
We just happened to pass through here.

370
00:36:34,600 --> 00:36:37,160
It's almost nightfall.
Stay here for the night.

371
00:36:37,240 --> 00:36:39,240
You can continue in the morning.

372
00:36:45,440 --> 00:36:46,280
That sounds good.

373
00:36:46,360 --> 00:36:49,120
I've been walking all day,
My legs are killing me.

374
00:36:50,880 --> 00:36:52,560
Alright. Come in.

375
00:36:52,640 --> 00:36:54,120
Come in.

376
00:36:55,760 --> 00:36:56,760
Let's go.

377
00:37:04,440 --> 00:37:07,680
Our village was attacked by another tribe.

378
00:37:07,760 --> 00:37:10,560
So we fled and settled deep
in the forest and mountains.

379
00:37:11,400 --> 00:37:13,200
What about your children?

380
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:15,880
They went to war. All of them died.

381
00:37:15,960 --> 00:37:18,640
Only the elderly remain now.

382
00:37:20,160 --> 00:37:22,320
If my son were still alive,

383
00:37:22,400 --> 00:37:25,320
he'd be about your age.

384
00:37:29,440 --> 00:37:31,360
You're lucky

385
00:37:31,440 --> 00:37:33,760
to have such a girl as your wife.

386
00:37:38,360 --> 00:37:41,040
So when will you have children?

387
00:37:45,920 --> 00:37:47,200
We're newly married.

388
00:37:48,240 --> 00:37:49,680
We're not thinking about children yet.

389
00:37:50,560 --> 00:37:53,440
Still, you should hurry and have them
soon, so they'll be grown in time.

390
00:37:55,720 --> 00:37:57,320
Alright.

391
00:38:00,320 --> 00:38:02,240
Here.

392
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:04,280
Wash your husband's feet.

393
00:38:07,320 --> 00:38:08,720
That's not necessary.

394
00:38:09,400 --> 00:38:10,800
I can wash them myself.

395
00:38:15,560 --> 00:38:16,440
No.

396
00:38:17,440 --> 00:38:19,160
It's our village custom.

397
00:38:19,240 --> 00:38:22,480
Before entering a home,
a wife must wash her husband's feet,

398
00:38:22,560 --> 00:38:24,320
so the couple will live long together.

399
00:38:27,640 --> 00:38:29,040
Fine. I'll do it.

400
00:39:06,240 --> 00:39:07,480
That's it, right?

401
00:39:08,640 --> 00:39:09,760
Not yet.

402
00:39:41,040 --> 00:39:44,320
What kind of tradition is this?
It's clearly oppressive to women.

403
00:39:44,840 --> 00:39:47,320
First washing feet, now bathing together.

404
00:39:49,120 --> 00:39:50,960
They say

405
00:39:51,040 --> 00:39:53,840
anyone staying overnight
must soak in the spring first,

406
00:39:53,920 --> 00:39:55,760
to cleanse the body completely.

407
00:40:02,880 --> 00:40:04,360
What are you looking at? Turn around.

408
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:07,160
Why are you shy?

409
00:40:08,040 --> 00:40:11,680
When you were bathing at the waterfall,
I saw everything.

410
00:40:13,080 --> 00:40:14,320
You pervert!

411
00:40:15,160 --> 00:40:16,200
See?

412
00:40:16,720 --> 00:40:20,400
If you'd slept in the forest with me,
we wouldn't be doing this now.

413
00:40:20,480 --> 00:40:24,000
This is your fault.
You told them I was your wife.

414
00:40:24,080 --> 00:40:28,560
I was worried
someone might take advantage of you.

415
00:40:29,240 --> 00:40:31,080
- Was that wrong?
- Yes.

416
00:40:31,160 --> 00:40:32,840
Wrong for caring about you?

417
00:40:33,560 --> 00:40:36,280
Wrong because you're not anything to me.

418
00:40:40,280 --> 00:40:43,520
Not yet. But soon enough.

419
00:40:45,280 --> 00:40:46,400
Or…

420
00:40:46,920 --> 00:40:48,160
should it be tonight?

421
00:40:51,160 --> 00:40:52,800
You pervert!

422
00:40:52,880 --> 00:40:54,200
Turn the other way.

423
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:11,280
How many families
live in this village, Uncle?

424
00:41:11,360 --> 00:41:13,760
Only four or five.

425
00:41:13,840 --> 00:41:17,560
During the day,
everyone goes hunting in the forest.

426
00:41:17,640 --> 00:41:20,520
At night, they return to sleep.

427
00:41:21,040 --> 00:41:23,680
We live quietly on our own.

428
00:41:23,760 --> 00:41:26,800
No wonder it's so peaceful.

429
00:41:26,880 --> 00:41:30,560
Unlike my village, where everyone
knows everyone else's business.

430
00:41:32,360 --> 00:41:35,000
If you like it here, you can stay with us.

431
00:41:38,800 --> 00:41:40,960
Let my wife return home.

432
00:41:41,040 --> 00:41:43,080
She can cook for me there.

433
00:41:43,760 --> 00:41:47,200
Good. A wife should
take care of her husband.

434
00:41:47,280 --> 00:41:50,120
A good daughter-in-law like this,
I approve.

435
00:41:55,280 --> 00:41:57,440
Here it is.

436
00:41:57,960 --> 00:42:00,320
Can you eat jungle food?

437
00:42:15,920 --> 00:42:16,920
Wow.

438
00:42:17,520 --> 00:42:20,320
It looks delicious.
Did you cook it yourself?

439
00:42:20,400 --> 00:42:21,400
Yes.

440
00:42:21,480 --> 00:42:24,160
We rarely get visitors,

441
00:42:24,240 --> 00:42:27,040
so I put my heart into it.

442
00:42:37,400 --> 00:42:39,200
Aren't you two eating with us?

443
00:42:39,280 --> 00:42:42,320
Go ahead. We're already full.

444
00:42:42,960 --> 00:42:45,640
Eat well. You'll sleep soundly.

445
00:42:45,720 --> 00:42:48,840
Then I won't hold back.

446
00:42:48,920 --> 00:42:49,960
Yeah.

447
00:43:28,560 --> 00:43:30,080
I'm going back to Tha Khiri.

448
00:43:33,720 --> 00:43:35,040
Why?

449
00:43:35,120 --> 00:43:36,600
To kill Pud.

450
00:43:40,160 --> 00:43:42,000
He's the village chief at Khuan Phra-ngam.

451
00:43:43,040 --> 00:43:44,440
If I want him dead,

452
00:43:45,440 --> 00:43:46,320
I have to go there.

453
00:43:53,440 --> 00:43:55,040
I shouldn't have trusted him.

454
00:43:56,280 --> 00:43:57,600
Because of me,

455
00:43:58,560 --> 00:43:59,840
Khun Yod had to die.

456
00:44:03,400 --> 00:44:06,000
Khun Yod's fate had ended.

457
00:44:07,200 --> 00:44:08,520
No one could have saved him.

458
00:44:08,600 --> 00:44:10,320
But if my father knew

459
00:44:11,080 --> 00:44:12,840
I worked with Pud to kill Khun Yod,

460
00:44:15,320 --> 00:44:16,880
he'd hate me.

461
00:44:18,960 --> 00:44:21,160
Father Wad will never find out.

462
00:44:23,440 --> 00:44:25,480
Once you kill Pud,

463
00:44:26,000 --> 00:44:29,680
your secret dies with him.

464
00:44:57,080 --> 00:44:58,400
Yiwha…

465
00:44:59,360 --> 00:45:00,760
where are you right now?

466
00:45:09,280 --> 00:45:10,160
Hey!

467
00:45:14,880 --> 00:45:15,960
Hey!

468
00:45:19,360 --> 00:45:20,440
Wad!

469
00:45:21,720 --> 00:45:25,080
Were you trying to kill me or what, Niem?

470
00:45:25,160 --> 00:45:27,240
What decent person shows up like that?

471
00:45:29,240 --> 00:45:30,440
How's my daughter?

472
00:45:40,840 --> 00:45:44,520
What was she thinking,
running off to find Lasor?

473
00:45:46,840 --> 00:45:48,960
It's not strange.
She went after her brother.

474
00:45:49,600 --> 00:45:51,160
Those two love each other deeply.

475
00:45:51,960 --> 00:45:53,440
They'd die for one another.

476
00:45:54,800 --> 00:45:56,840
Old Master Khrua Phut
projected his spirit to see me.

477
00:45:56,920 --> 00:45:59,680
If they were at Khao Phrom,
he would've told me.

478
00:46:01,200 --> 00:46:02,280
Where could she have gone?

479
00:46:07,080 --> 00:46:08,560
Men are hard to trust.

480
00:46:09,360 --> 00:46:11,480
I don't want to see you cry.

481
00:46:11,560 --> 00:46:13,800
Keep that bracelet hidden well.

482
00:46:14,320 --> 00:46:15,640
Don't let your father see it.

483
00:46:16,400 --> 00:46:18,760
Or could she be following that young man?

484
00:46:20,480 --> 00:46:21,440
Who?

485
00:46:22,080 --> 00:46:23,280
Who is he?

486
00:46:23,360 --> 00:46:24,600
I don't know.

487
00:46:25,120 --> 00:46:27,720
I only know that Yiwha is in love.

488
00:46:31,640 --> 00:46:33,280
I'm going to bring her back.

489
00:46:33,360 --> 00:46:34,520
Where will you go?

490
00:46:34,600 --> 00:46:38,200
Anywhere. Everywhere.
I've already lost my son.

491
00:46:38,880 --> 00:46:40,680
I will not lose my daughter too.

492
00:47:14,120 --> 00:47:15,280
I'll sleep outside.

493
00:47:15,360 --> 00:47:16,440
Hey.

494
00:47:16,520 --> 00:47:19,480
Stay here.
If you leave, they might get suspicious.

495
00:47:29,000 --> 00:47:31,400
Then you sleep over there.
I'll sleep here.

496
00:47:34,680 --> 00:47:38,240
It gets cold at night.
Sleeping closer to me is warmer.

497
00:47:39,080 --> 00:47:41,200
I get hot easily.
I don't like sleeping next to anyone.

498
00:48:18,000 --> 00:48:19,560
Why are you staring at me?

499
00:48:20,160 --> 00:48:23,040
If I look at your face, I'll sleep well.

500
00:48:24,040 --> 00:48:26,920
But I can't sleep. Turn the other way,

501
00:48:27,000 --> 00:48:28,640
or I'll poke your eyes out.

502
00:48:49,960 --> 00:48:51,040
What's wrong?

503
00:48:51,560 --> 00:48:53,800
Someone was peeking over there.

504
00:48:59,160 --> 00:49:01,400
Where? I don't see anyone.

505
00:49:10,520 --> 00:49:12,440
But I really saw someone there.

506
00:49:36,080 --> 00:49:37,320
You imagined it, Orror.

507
00:49:58,840 --> 00:50:02,000
This side is my bed. Yours is over there.

508
00:50:05,160 --> 00:50:08,560
I'm sleeping here.
You go sleep over there.

509
00:50:08,640 --> 00:50:12,080
No. I like sleeping here.

510
00:50:12,960 --> 00:50:14,080
Ouch.

511
00:50:14,640 --> 00:50:16,480
It's uncomfortable.

512
00:50:17,640 --> 00:50:18,760
Just sleep.

513
00:50:19,640 --> 00:50:20,960
It's only one night.

514
00:50:23,600 --> 00:50:24,680
I'm sleepy.

515
00:50:34,040 --> 00:50:35,120
- Share it with me too.
- Hey!

516
00:50:35,640 --> 00:50:37,240
Blur.

517
00:50:39,040 --> 00:50:40,080
Let go.

518
00:51:12,200 --> 00:51:13,240
Orror?

519
00:51:20,960 --> 00:51:22,000
Orror.

520
00:51:29,200 --> 00:51:30,240
Orror.

521
00:51:35,000 --> 00:51:36,040
Orror.

522
00:51:37,240 --> 00:51:38,240
Orror.

523
00:52:18,400 --> 00:52:22,160
That food was laced with suppressants.
It's blocking my sorcery.

524
00:52:27,240 --> 00:52:29,360
It must've been that couple.

525
00:52:36,240 --> 00:52:37,240
Orror.

526
00:52:38,760 --> 00:52:39,680
Orror.

527
00:52:40,520 --> 00:52:41,520
Orror.

528
00:52:43,560 --> 00:52:44,600
Orror.

529
00:52:45,520 --> 00:52:46,560
Orror.

530
00:52:49,120 --> 00:52:50,280
Orror.

531
00:53:08,840 --> 00:53:10,120
What is this?

532
00:53:28,760 --> 00:53:31,800
Tonight, our son will finally have a wife.

533
00:53:33,600 --> 00:53:37,560
At last, we can die in peace.

534
00:53:42,760 --> 00:53:44,560
It's time to send the bride off.

535
00:53:47,720 --> 00:53:51,320
<i>Om, orang mati mejadi damai</i>

536
00:53:52,640 --> 00:53:56,680
<i>Om, orang mati mejadi damai</i>

537
00:53:57,680 --> 00:54:01,840
<i>Om, orang mati mejadi damai</i>

538
00:54:02,360 --> 00:54:05,520
<i>Spirits of the dead, unite with the living</i>

539
00:54:06,120 --> 00:54:08,680
<i>Spirits of the dead, unite with the living</i>

540
00:54:08,760 --> 00:54:11,440
- <i>Om, orang mati mejadi damai</i>
- <i>Spirits of the dead</i>

541
00:54:11,520 --> 00:54:13,080
<i>Unite with the living</i>

542
00:54:13,160 --> 00:54:17,520
- <i>Om, orang mati mejadi damai</i>
- <i>Spirits of the dead…</i>

543
00:54:17,600 --> 00:54:21,280
<i>Om, orang mati mejadi damai</i>

544
00:54:22,320 --> 00:54:23,400
Uncle, Auntie,

545
00:54:23,480 --> 00:54:24,640
please let me go.

546
00:54:25,160 --> 00:54:27,880
Little girl,
you must become my daughter-in-law.

547
00:54:50,080 --> 00:54:51,320
Blur!

548
00:54:55,480 --> 00:54:57,680
- You ruined my son's wedding!
- Watch out!

549
00:55:39,040 --> 00:55:42,640
Two of my prophecies
have already come true.

550
00:55:44,080 --> 00:55:47,840
First, within three days,
your wife will die by a venomous creature.

551
00:55:48,640 --> 00:55:51,880
Second, your son will bring great ruin

552
00:55:51,960 --> 00:55:54,200
upon Chum Suea.

553
00:55:56,280 --> 00:56:01,040
Only one remains. Just one more.

554
00:56:02,280 --> 00:56:03,640
That's not a prophecy.

555
00:56:04,800 --> 00:56:06,200
It's a curse.

556
00:56:06,280 --> 00:56:09,080
Prophecy or curse,

557
00:56:09,160 --> 00:56:11,200
you cannot escape it.

558
00:56:11,960 --> 00:56:15,200
The more you chase your daughter,

559
00:56:15,280 --> 00:56:18,400
the closer death draws to you.

560
00:56:18,480 --> 00:56:20,240
I'm not afraid to die.

561
00:56:22,120 --> 00:56:24,840
But I won't let my child
carry the sin of killing her father.

562
00:56:25,360 --> 00:56:28,000
Those twins

563
00:56:28,080 --> 00:56:31,040
share a bound fate.

564
00:56:31,120 --> 00:56:35,480
If one dies, the other will follow,

565
00:56:35,560 --> 00:56:37,880
within three days, seven at most.

566
00:56:41,760 --> 00:56:44,080
<i>This must be the cave.</i>
<i>Perfect for Lek Lai.</i>

567
00:56:45,080 --> 00:56:49,240
<i>Om, sawa hom mama mama</i>
<i>narakja cittang phanthanang.</i>

568
00:56:50,080 --> 00:56:52,000
<i>Your daughter is not here.</i>

569
00:56:52,080 --> 00:56:54,840
I've searched for her in every direction,

570
00:56:55,360 --> 00:56:56,800
yet found no trace.

571
00:56:56,880 --> 00:56:58,800
<i>It's the power of the Klaikot Lek Lai.</i>

572
00:56:58,880 --> 00:57:00,960
<i>I saw it vanish into your body.</i>

573
00:57:01,040 --> 00:57:02,000
Blur!

574
00:57:02,080 --> 00:57:04,120
Stop right there. Don't move.

575
00:57:04,200 --> 00:57:07,560
A bandit like you must die
so the land can rise higher.

576
00:57:07,640 --> 00:57:08,640
Bandit this.

577
00:57:08,720 --> 00:57:10,120
Bandit that.

578
00:57:10,640 --> 00:57:12,520
<i>The governor has appointed Lasor</i>

579
00:57:12,600 --> 00:57:16,240
<i>as the new village chief</i>
<i>of Khuan Phra-ngam, replacing Pud.</i>

580
00:57:16,320 --> 00:57:18,160
Please don't die, Blur.

581
00:58:07,720 --> 00:58:09,920
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
